=============================================================================
HOW TO USE THIS FILE (adopter / per-repo notes -- NOT part of the License)
=============================================================================

This file is the Single Source of Truth (SSoT) template for the HyperI
Business Source License 1.1 (BUSL-1.1) community licence. Each consuming
repository copies this file and fills in the per-repo parameters described
below. The text BELOW the line "=== BEGIN LICENSE ===" is the canonical
Business Source License 1.1, reproduced verbatim, with ONLY the adopter
parameter fields filled in (the four BSL parameters plus the Additional Use
Grant). Do not edit any other word of the License body: BSL Covenant 4
forbids modifying the License text in any other way.

Per-repo parameters each consuming repository MUST set:

  Licensor:        Fixed for all HyperI repos --
                   HYPERI PTY LIMITED (ABN 31 622 581 748).

  Licensed Work:   Set per repo. Replace the placeholder
                   <LICENSED WORK: [repository name], Copyright (c) [year]
                   HYPERI PTY LIMITED> with the repository / product name and
                   the copyright year of that version's release. Example:
                   "HyperI Example 1.4. The Licensed Work is (c) 2026
                   HYPERI PTY LIMITED."

  Change Date:     Set per VERSION, NOT once per repo. The rule is a rolling,
                   per-version Change Date equal to that version's release
                   date plus THREE (3) YEARS. The BSL frame caps the Change
                   Date at the fourth anniversary of first publication
                   (see the "fourth anniversary" sentence in the Terms); a
                   shorter Change Date is permitted, and HyperI deliberately
                   chooses 3 years. Because "This License applies separately
                   for each version of the Licensed Work and the Change Date
                   may vary for each version" (Terms), each released version
                   carries its own Change Date = its release date + 3 years.
                   Release dates are recorded in the GitHub release history.
                   Set the Change Date field below to the concrete calendar
                   date (release date + 3 years) for the version being
                   shipped.

  Change License:  Fixed for all HyperI repos -- Apache License, Version 2.0.

Additional instruments (each independently severable, each OUTSIDE this
License text, none incorporated as a condition of the BSL grant):

  - LICENSE-RIDER-AFFILIATE.md   (affiliate / corporate-group terms)
  - LICENSE-RIDER-AUSTRALIA.md   (Australian-law overlay)
  - AI-TRAINING-POLICY.md        (AI / machine-learning terms)

COUNSEL FLAGS in this file:
  - The Additional Use Grant below is the ONE HyperI-novel splice. It is
    marked inline [HYPERI-NOVEL -- COUNSEL MUST BLESS].
  - The "License text copyright (c) 2017 MariaDB Corporation Ab" line and the
    trademark line are reproduced from the SPDX-registered BUSL-1.1 text and
    the CockroachDB v21.2.0 BSL.txt (both carry the 2017 MariaDB Corporation
    Ab form). The live mariadb.com/bsl11 page now renders "(c) 2024 MariaDB
    plc". Counsel must confirm which form is canonical for HyperI; the
    2017 form is reproduced here because it is the stable SPDX BUSL-1.1
    boilerplate and matches real adopter files.
  - License text is reproduced with straight ASCII quotation marks. The
    canonical source renders typographic (curly) quotation marks in the
    defined-term quotes and apostrophes. The normalisation to ASCII is
    cosmetic and changes no operative word; counsel may restore typographic
    quotes if preferred.

