                      [HYPERI-NOVEL -- COUNSEL MUST BLESS: the only
                      adopter-novel content in this License. Built on the
                      verbatim CockroachDB BSL 1.1 Additional Use Grant
                      skeleton (the "You may make use ... provided that you
                      may not use ... for a [term]. A '[term]' is a
                      commercial offering that allows third parties (other
                      than your employees and contractors) to access the
                      functionality of the Licensed Work" sentence, kept
                      word-for-word including the employee/contractor
                      carve), with two changes: (1) the defined term
                      "Database Service" renamed to "Hosted Service"; and
                      (2) the CockroachDB database-specific tail "by creating
                      tables whose schemas are controlled by such third
                      parties" replaced with a service-provision tail adapted
                      from the Elastic License 2.0 hosted/managed-service
                      limitation. This Additional Use Grant contains ONLY the
                      service-provision scope limit. It contains NO affiliate,
                      Australian-law, or AI terms -- BSL Covenant 2 requires
                      the Additional Use Grant not to impose additional
                      restrictions, so those terms live in the separable
                      instruments listed in the adopter notes above, never
                      in this Grant. Counsel must (a) confirm this boundary
                      reads as a scope limit on the Grant (permissible) and
                      not as an additional restriction on the base grant
                      (forbidden by Covenant 2), and (b) decide whether to
                      define "a substantial set of the features or
                      functionality" or accept that inherited ambiguity.]

